      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hydrogen peroxide is too harsh for an open wound; it can actually damage the healing tissue, so avoid that completely. Neosporin is a good over-the-counter option, but if you want maximum effect, look for a cream containing Bacitracin or Mupirocin, which are excellent topical antibiotics. Keep applying it twice a day, and if the warmth increases or you develop any fever, you must stop self-treating and seek professional advice.",
